GitLab Flow

Used heavily in GitLab.

It combines environment-based branches with feature branches.

Layman Explanation

Think of different stages of deployment:

Development → Testing → Production

Code moves through these stages.

feature/login
      |
      v
develop
      |
      v
pre-production
      |
      v
production

Explanation

Branches represent environments.

Example:

feature branch → develop → staging → production

This helps teams control deployment stages.

Interview Answer

GitLab Flow extends GitHub Flow by adding environment branches such as staging or production, enabling better control over deployments and release management.

Advantages

Supports CI/CD pipelines

Good environment control

Easier than Git Flow

Disadvantages

Slightly more complex than GitHub Flow
